# VIXL Import Provenance

This file records the exact VIXL upstream baseline that the AArch64 simulator
code under `src/` and `src/aarch64/` was imported from. It is the anchor for
the `// gaby-vm:` marker convention: every modification inside an imported
file is auditable as a deviation from the commit recorded here.

## Imported baseline

- **Upstream**: https://github.com/Linaro/vixl
- **Commit (full)**: `3fe16863216491846caa02ea8eaa746411526e4a`
- **Commit (short)**: `3fe16863`
- **Commit date**: 2026-05-06 17:58:05 +0100
- **Commit subject**: Faster IsLeafNode() check in the decoder
- **Imported on**: 2026-05-08

## Re-sync procedure (manual)

1. Update the local VIXL working tree (`../vixl`) to a newer upstream commit.
2. Run `git grep -nE 'gaby-vm( BEGIN| END|:)' src/` to enumerate every
   Gaby-VM-local modification of the imported files.
3. For each imported file under `src/` and `src/aarch64/`, three-way merge
   the upstream change against the marker-protected Gaby-VM regions.
4. Update the commit hash above to the new baseline.

The marker convention is documented in
`openspec/changes/extract-vixl-aarch64-simulator-baseline/design.md` (decision
D5) and in the spec under `specs/aarch64-simulator/spec.md` (requirement R4).
